widgets_values: The first pass is split in two tiles. The nodes below take care of calculating the right size and position of each in both landscape and portrait mode.
Works better with scale factor from ~1.1 to ~1.7.

You will find 3 prompts marked green in the workflow.

The one below for the global composition and two more for each tile. Depending on the image you may get better result by prompting the tiles accurately. Sometimes small changes make a huge difference.

===================================
FLUX [dev] Latent Upscaler/Detailer
===================================

I made this workflow because sometimes Flux generates low detailed images. Noise injection, upscaling and composition is all done in the LATENT space to avoid unnecessary VAE decodes. Personally I disable all the previews and just wait for the final result.

This is not meant as an upscaler per-se, latent upscale is not great to begin with. You will NOT get a more detailed version of the original first pass, just a more detailed image in general.
